    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "3a4c3053a5745014",
      "text": "Of course, I got really excited with the idea and had to turn it into code. After all, that is the epitome of declarative programming! The paper is really readable, and I urge you to take a look at it. There are many mathematical details that I will not touch and even a whole discussion on how these same techniques apply to Laplace transforms. As an appetizer of what we are going to do, consider the initial value problem y'' = -x^2 y + 2 y' + 4 \\\\ y(0) = 0,\\; y'(0) = 1."
